Hours passed, and the night began to fall.
 Zorian still continued to wander the streets of the city, restless.
 Though he had no real emergency to worry about, it somehow felt wrong to him
 to just lay around and do nothing.
 He had spent so much time constantly on the move, constantly tackling one
